'''Secrets''' in Final Fantasy Mystic Quest include hidden items, optional content, and gameplay tips.

== Hidden Battlefields ==

Some battlefields are not immediately obvious:
* Check all areas of the overworld
* Some appear after story events
* Revisit areas for missed battlefields

== Secret Items ==

=== Mega Grenades ===
Most powerful consumable attack item.

'''Locations:'''
* Later dungeons
* Hidden chests
* Limited supply

=== Cure Potions ===
Best healing items found in:
* Focus Tower sections
* Hidden chests
* Some battlefield rewards

== Battlefield Secrets ==

=== Completion Rewards ===
Clearing all 10 battles on a battlefield:
* Fixed item reward
* Experience points
* Cannot be repeated after completion

=== Battle Count ===
Each battlefield has exactly 10 encounters:
* Counter visible on battlefield screen
* Rewards given at exactly 10 clears
* Enemies get harder as counter increases

== Hidden Passages ==

=== Jump Points ===
Benjamin can jump to reach hidden areas:
* Look for ledges and gaps
* Some areas require specific approach angles
* Hidden chests often behind jumps

=== Bombable Walls ===
Certain walls can be destroyed:
* Use bombs on suspicious walls
* Often contain passages to secrets
* Required for some progression

=== Axe-able Trees ===
Trees blocking paths:
* Cut with axe after obtaining
* Reveal shortcuts
* Some hide item locations

== Companion Secrets ==

=== Companion Abilities ===
Each companion has different focus:
* Kaeli - Nature magic
* Tristam - Physical attacks
* Phoebe - Status magic
* Reuben - Combat skills

=== Companion Items ===
Companions may carry items:
* Check their inventories
* Some have unique equipment
* Items transfer when they leave

== Weapon Tricks ==

=== Axe Properties ===
* Effective against plant enemies
* Can cut trees on overworld
* Good for multi-target

=== Bombs ===
* Destroy walls
* Fire damage
* Limited supply

=== Claws ===
* Climb walls
* Grapple points
* Essential for exploration

=== Sword ===
* Most balanced weapon
* Effective on most enemies
* Standard damage type

== Magic Secrets ==

=== Spell Charges ===
Each spell type has separate charges:
* White magic - healing and support
* Black magic - offensive spells
* Wizard magic - utility spells

=== Charge Restoration ===
Charges restore at:
* Inns
* Certain save points
* Full party heal locations

== Tips ==

'''Combat:'''
* Exploit weaknesses for extra damage
* Status effects are very useful
* Don't waste consumables early

'''Exploration:'''
* Return to areas with new tools
* Check all corners
* Some secrets require multiple visits

'''Boss Fights:'''
* Heal before engaging
* Use companions effectively
* Status effects work on some bosses

== Easter Eggs ==

=== Final Fantasy References ===
* Music contains FF series callbacks
* Monster designs reference other games
* Spell names match FF series

=== Developer Room ===
Some versions have hidden content areas accessible via glitches.

== Difficulty Notes ==

FFMQ is considered an entry-level RPG:
* Lower difficulty than other FF games
* Designed for new RPG players
* Optional content provides challenge

